      <div class="msgContentFrame">In your Actions &amp; Traits menu, go down to the &quot;Ability&quot; section and add the crafting traits.  Every discipline of the hand, at level 10, gives you a unique trait. <br /> <br />If you're on armorer and wish to use alchemists's preserve for example,  you can add it as one your abilities. <br /> <br />Once you add whatever ability you want to use, while crafting, it will randomly show up as one of your options.  So you'll see standard/rapid/bold/wait... and then potentially 1 or 2 of the abilities you added.  At that point you can select it to activate it.  Most abilities last on average 3 rounds of crafting, where a 'wait' commands counts as a round.</div>
      <div class="msgFtFrame">
